U.S. Treasury Department Schedule for Thursday, June 16

-- B y   V i n c e n t   D e l   G i u d i c e
-- 
2011-06-16T13:14:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/u-s-treasury-department-schedule-for-thursday-june-16.html
The following is a reformatted
version of the U.S. Treasury Department’s daily release on the
schedule for Secretary Timothy F. Geithner and other officials:  On Thursday morning, Secretary Geithner will meet with
members of the  Business Roundtable  for a discussion on the
Administration’s agenda for promoting job creation and economic
growth, addressing our fiscal challenges, and boosting the
competitiveness of U.S. firms. This meeting is closed press.  In the afternoon, the Secretary will attend the Vice
President’s next meeting of the bipartisan, bicameral group of
Members of Congress to continue work on a legislative framework
for comprehensive deficit reduction. Participants in the meeting
will include the Vice President, Senator Daniel Inouye, Senator
 Jon Kyl , Senator  Max Baucus , Representative Eric Cantor,
Representative James Clyburn, Representative Chris Van Hollen,
Director of the Office of Management and Budget Jacob Lew, and
Director of the National Economic Council Gene Sperling. This
meeting at the U.S. Capitol is closed press.  Later in the afternoon, Secretary Geithner will meet with
the Financial Stability Oversight Board at Treasury. This
meeting is closed press.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Del Giudice in  Washington  
 vdelgiudice@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at   cwellisz@bloomberg.net  